parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, slip, or hesitate while shifting gears, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The transmission jerks or slips when shifting gears
the vehicle surges or hesitates when accelerating
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the vehicle accelerates without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk while driving, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or jerks when shifting gears
the vehicle hesitates or loses power
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle surges or accelerates without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to shift gears can cause the vehicle to become stuck in one gear, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The transmission fails to shift into gear
the vehicle is stuck in one gear
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle position sensor can cause the vehicle to hesitate or accelerate without warning, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or accelerates without warning
the throttle position sensor fails
the vehicle's engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shifter can cause the vehicle to become stuck in one gear, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The gear shifter fails to engage
the vehicle is stuck in one gear
the gear shifter makes unusual noises
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended movement of the driver's seat can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses. This can be particularly dangerous if the seat moves while the vehicle is in motion, making it difficult for the driver to reach the pedals or maintain control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The driver's seat moves unexpectedly
often to the "easy egress" position
while the vehicle is in motion or stationary. The interior lights may also come on simultaneously. The seat may move back and forth repeatedly
making it difficult for the driver to maintain control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch and Seat Control Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch and seat control module can cause the driver's seat to move unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents. Additionally, the malfunctioning seat can cause the interior lights to turn on and off, creating a distraction for the driver.
symptoms: The driver's seat moves back and forth or adjusts itself while driving
the interior lights turn on and off
the seatbelt locks and unlocks unexpectedly
the vehicle's ignition switch is loose
and the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle's transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power and control, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into limp mode
the transmission shifts incorrectly
the torque converter fails
and the electrical components fry.
